	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 9th 7:04 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The other day, after pestering my guild and finally getting a 30-35 lvl group to go (there were 4 of us with a lvl 45 druid back-up) to go and camp for my ghoulbane in U Guk from the Shin Lord.&nbsp;&nbsp;When we first arrived in Guk we automatically did a camp check and nobody responded to the shin lord's room.  So, after having invis and see invis casted upon us by or enchanter off we went.  When we got there there was a lvl 45 iskar monk sitting in the room waiting for the shin lord spawn.  I knew immediatly what he was doing but I asked anyway- "what are you camping a green lvl monster for with the exception of the loot?"  His response was that he was getting the ghoulbane for his alternate character.  He shortly left the area and stated that I had stole his camp.  I explained to him the whole need vs. greed (for lack of a better word) mantra that we live by.  I told him if he has a problem with me "camp stealing" then to petition me and my entire guild for it, and that the GB was something that any respecting palidian would earn rather than farm or buy for.  I said that I have a major problem of high-lvl people camping for a rare spawn with an even rarer drop when they could be off somwhere else gaining exp and decent loot for that character so that they can sell it for an exobatant amount or give it to a low level alt (nothing I hate more than the sight I say days earlier- a lvl 10 dwarve pali in full DW armor and wielding Wurmslayer).  I told him if he wants the GB he should bring his palidan alt with a group and earn it like anyone else should.  Long story short I didn't get my GB that night, the ppl in the party were getting sleepy so we tp'ed outta there, but we did kill the shin lord (only had a rusty long sword and a bracer on).  I will attempt it later on, but I sure wished that Verant would have made the Ghoulbane a no-drop.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></tr>
