	   <tr><td colspan=2>You know, everytime I see an auction to sell Ghoulbane, I check and see a non-paladin hi lvl character sellin it for outrageous price. Well maybe his giving up his paladin character and is selling the GB but hey why would anyone in his right mind give up a noble and fun playin class like the Paladins.<br><br>So he must be a farmer farming the GB to sell to those uber Paladins that dont mind spendin 2k to get our undead-bashing sword, while the rest of us that take 30 lvls to connect a network of friends you can trust to be in a group to camp for your Ghoulbane, have to watch helplessly a lvl 45 non-paladin farmer stealin our camp from right under our righteous nose<br><br>That is what disgust me - moolah grubbin characters in the game that milk Norrath for all the money its worth and make other players life miserable<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
